Package org.anchoranalysis.feature.cache.calculate

  • Interface Summary 
    Interface Description
    CacheCreator  
    CalculateForChild<T extends FeatureInput>
    Performs calculations using child-caches instead of the main cache
    CalculationResolver<T extends FeatureInput>
    Searches a cache to reuses a FeatureCalculation if it already exists.
    FeatureSessionCache<T extends FeatureInput>
    A context in which to calculate features while caching certain duplicated internal calculations among the features.
    FeatureSessionCacheCalculator<T extends FeatureInput>
    Calculates features in the context of a particular {#FeatureSessionCache}.
    ResettableCalculation
    A calculation that be invalidated (resetted), removing any existing cached value.
  • Class Summary 
    Class Description
    CacheableCalculation<S,​T extends FeatureInput,​E extends Exception>
    Caches the result of a calculation, until reset() is called
    CacheableCalculationMap<S,​T extends FeatureInput,​U,​E extends Exception>
    Similar to a CacheableCalculation but stores several evaluations parameterised by a key
    FeatureCalculation<S,​T extends FeatureInput>  
    ResolvedCalculation<S,​T extends FeatureInput>
    Like a CacheableCalculation but has been resolved against a cache to ensure its unique (singular).
    ResolvedCalculationMap<S,​T extends FeatureInput,​U>
    A CacheableCalculationMap that has been resolved against a cache.
